history.content:
After the drop deadline, the CalCentral system should drop you automatically if you're not enrolled (read: on the waitlist) for the class with no fee, though it might take a couple of days for the system to reflect that. Actually, I don't believe you are even allowed to manually drop after the deadline, so you should be fine.

Hope you get into whatever class you're waitlisted for though!

EDIT: If you were referring to tomorrow's no fee drop deadline, please see the instructor's answer. Thanks Nicole!

I think the student is referring to the earlier deadline, which incurs a $10 fee. Tomorrow is the deadline to drop a class without a $10 fee. It is also the deadline to drop CS 162

The deadline to drop all non "early-drop deadline" courses is Feb 17th. 

Unfortunately, I do not know the answer to the original question. I believe Cal Student Central would.
Does dropping a waitlisted class after the drop deadline incur a fee/fine?
